  <prompt>
    Build `FinancialCalculatorHandler` — a pure-deterministic `IToolHandler` implementation
    per FR-18 that performs financial math on extracted figures. Examples: sum a list of
    line-item amounts; compute tax (rate × subtotal); compute discount (subtotal − rate ×
    subtotal); convert currencies (using a fixed FX-rate table from `sprk_configuration`,
    NOT a live FX call); compute weighted averages; aggregate by category. NO LLM call.
    NO Azure OpenAI dependency. Pure C# `decimal` arithmetic (NEVER `double` for money).

    Handler registers via auto-discovery per task 100's contract — implements `IToolHandler`;
    `HandlerId = "FinancialCalculatorHandler"`; lives in
    `Services/Ai/Handlers/FinancialCalculatorHandler.cs`. Requires corresponding
    `sprk_analysistool` row with `sprk_handlerclass = "FinancialCalculatorHandler"` +
    `sprk_configuration` JSON specifying `supportedCurrencies`, `fxRateTable` (currency-pair
    keyed), `defaultRoundingMode` (e.g., BankersRounding), `decimalPrecision` (default 2).

    Configurable behavior per FR-18 acceptance: handler accepts optional configuration
    from the tool row; output is identical for identical input + same config. All money
    math uses `decimal`. Telemetry per ADR-015.

    Tests: contract test + positive cases (sum, tax, discount, currency conversion,
    weighted avg, aggregation) + error cases (negative amount where forbidden, unknown
    currency code, division by zero) + config-driven test (different rounding modes
    produce different deterministic outputs).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with .NET 8 + financial-math experience. Understands `decimal`
    vs `double` for money, banker's rounding, ISO 4217 currency codes, and the
    correctness consequences of FX precision.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `FinancialCalculatorHandler.cs` implemented in `Services/Ai/Handlers/`; auto-discovered;
    `sprk_analysistool` row deployed with `sprk_handlerclass = "FinancialCalculatorHandler"`;
    unit tests cover positive + error + config-driven cases including all standard
    financial operations; ZERO LLM/Azure-OpenAI dependencies; all money math uses
    `decimal`; BFF publish-size delta ≤+0.5 MB; `code-review` + `adr-check` green.
  </goal>

