  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL">
      Check context. If &gt;70%, run `context-handoff` then `/compact`. Declare:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: New BFF handler; financial math correctness; Pillar 2 binding rule; FR-18
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: all 11 steps below including Step 9.5 quality gates
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`; confirm 102 is 🔲; dependency 100 is complete.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Extract from
      `HandlerRegistrationConventions.md` (created by task 100) the 4-point contract.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Design Handler Surface">
      Define: `HandlerId = "FinancialCalculatorHandler"`; supported operations enum
      (Sum, Tax, Discount, FxConvert, WeightedAvg, AggregateByCategory); `ConfigSchema`
      with `supportedCurrencies`, `fxRateTable`, `defaultRoundingMode`, `decimalPrecision`.
      NO `IOpenAiClient` dependency.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Handler">
      Create `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/FinancialCalculatorHandler.cs`.
      All money math uses `decimal`. Implement each operation with explicit rounding mode.
      FX conversion uses the configured `fxRateTable` ONLY — no live FX calls. Validate
      input figures are non-null + appropriately signed per operation.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Author Unit Tests">
      Create `FinancialCalculatorHandlerTests.cs` using `TypedToolHandlerTestFixture`.
      Cover: contract test; positive (sum, tax = 8.25% × subtotal rounded banker, discount
      10%, USD→EUR FX, weighted avg, aggregate by category); error (unknown currency,
      negative tax rate, division by zero, missing fxRateTable entry); config-driven
      (BankersRounding vs MidpointAwayFromZero produce different deterministic outputs);
      telemetry compliance.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Seed sprk_analysistool Row">
      Create `infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-financial-calculator-row.json` with
      `sprk_handlerclass = "FinancialCalculatorHandler"`, `sprk_toolcode = "FIN-CALC@v1"`,
      sample `sprk_configuration`, `AvailableInContexts = "Playbook"`. Deploy to Spaarke
      Dev. Capture evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify Build + Tests">
      `dotnet build` + targeted `dotnet test --filter "FinancialCalculatorHandler"`. Both
      pass. Auto-discovery verification picks up handler.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify BFF Publish-Size Delta">
      `dotnet publish -c Release ... -o deploy/api-publish/`. Report absolute + diff vs
      baseline. Target ≤+0.5 MB.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through criteria; record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` + `adr-check`. Both MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task status `complete`; TASK-INDEX 102 🔲 → ✅; reset `current-task.md`.
    </step>
  </steps>

